<!-- ══ 05 FAILURE SCENARIOS ══ -->
<section class="section" id="scenarios">
  <div class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-n">05</span><span class="eyebrow-l">Risk Analysis</span></div>
  <h2 class="section-heading">Failure Scenarios</h2>
  <p class="section-lead">The following scenarios show how each architecture behaves under common failure conditions — a primary reason for the Option 1 recommendation.</p>
  <div class="section-rule"></div>

  <h3 class="subsm">Scenario A — Planned DMS Database Maintenance (30-minute window)</h3>
  <div class="sc-pair">
    <div class="sc-card suc">
      <div class="sc-hd suc"><div class="sc-icon">✅</div><div><div class="sc-title">Option 1 — With SQS</div><div class="sc-sub">Zero data loss · Automatic recovery</div></div></div>
      <div class="sc-bd">
        <div class="tr-row"><div class="t-time">10:00 AM</div><div class="t-ev">DMS database taken offline for maintenance</div></div>
        <div class="tr-row"><div class="t-time">10:05 AM</div><div class="t-ev">SAP releases 50 orders — all 50 enqueued in SQS</div></div>
        <div class="tr-row"><div class="t-time">10:15 AM</div><div class="t-ev">Lambda picks up messages from SQS — DB write fails, messages stay in queue</div></div>
        <div class="tr-row"><div class="t-time">10:20 AM</div><div class="t-ev">30 more orders arrive — also queued. 80 total waiting in SQS</div></div>
        <div class="tr-row"><div class="t-time">10:30 AM</div><div class="t-ev t-good">DMS database back online ✓</div></div>
        <div class="tr-row"><div class="t-time">10:32 AM</div><div class="t-ev t-good">Lambda drains all 80 messages into staging automatically ✓</div></div>
        <div class="sc-verdict">✓ Zero data loss<br>✓ No manual intervention<br>✓ Recovery in ~2 minutes</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="sc-card fail">
      <div class="sc-hd fail"><div class="sc-icon">❌</div><div><div class="sc-title">Option 2 — Direct Write</div><div class="sc-sub">Permanent data loss · Manual recovery</div></div></div>
      <div class="sc-bd">
        <div class="tr-row"><div class="t-time">10:00 AM</div><div class="t-ev">DMS database taken offline for maintenance</div></div>
        <div class="tr-row"><div class="t-time">10:05 AM</div><div class="t-ev">SAP releases 50 orders — direct DB write attempted</div></div>
        <div class="tr-row"><div class="t-time">10:05 AM</div><div class="t-ev t-bad">All 50 writes fail — DMS unreachable. Orders permanently lost ✗</div></div>
        <div class="tr-row"><div class="t-time">10:30 AM</div><div class="t-ev">DMS database back online — staging table is empty</div></div>
        <div class="tr-row"><div class="t-time">11:00 AM</div><div class="t-ev t-bad">Production team alerts: 50 orders missing from DMS ✗</div></div>
        <div class="tr-row"><div class="t-time">12:00 PM</div><div class="t-ev t-bad">Manual re-fetch from SAP and re-insertion complete — 2hr delay ✗</div></div>
        <div class="sc-verdict">✗ 50 orders permanently lost<br>✗ Manual recovery required<br>✗ 2-hour production delay</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

